CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 28, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Death Plunge Avoided - Gene Robinson, 13, of 703 Chauncey Street, on Monday escaped a possible death plunge into an abandoned well which a cave-in uncovered near his backyard. The well, about fourteen feet in diameter, contains an unknown depth of water, twenty-five feet from the surface opening. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Gene Robinson squatting near abandoned well, with four shirtless boys peering through wire fence in background, Hill District
